   <body>
      <context/>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Only in systems with adjacent battery cabinet(s): Route the adjacent battery signal cables through the left side
panel of the UPS to the control terminal block TB1.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the cover on the UPS cabinet.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_50_kwups_removecoverbeforecomcable_w120mm_0000162184.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Unlock all the breakers.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the breaker cover on the UPS cabinet.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_50_kwups_unlockbreakersremovecover_w120mm_0000162183.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Route the signal cables through the top gland plate in
the top entry cabinet, into the cable channel, through the transformer
cabinet (if present), and into the UPS cabinet to the control terminal
block TB1. </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Route the signal cables through the top gland plate in
the top entry cabinet, into the cable channel, through the transformer
cabinet (if present), and into the UPS cabinet to the external connection
board 0P2553.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig expanse="page">
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet and Top Entry Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/25-50kva_ups_and_top_entry_cabinet_route_control_cables_170mm_0000125362.svg"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
               <fig expanse="page">
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet, Transformer Cabinet, and Top
Entry Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_50_kwsinglewtransformer_routewaysignalcable_w170mm_0000162696.svg"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Reinstall the covers in the UPS cabinet.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
